            "content": {
                "raw": "Hi Britton, I have reviewed the code changes.\n\nOverall, I like this direction.  I was a bit confused about the distinction between SimulationTimeSeries and TimeSeriesData, but I think I now understand it.  The SimulationTimeSeries acts as a \"value added\" mechanism of adding a few routines, as well as a self-registering mechanism, to simulation data.  This definitely works.\n\nOne question I had was if you see this as potentially being a more flat relationship between the classes -- i.e., TimeSeriesData being the base class, with SimulationTimeSeries inheriting (and remaining basically the same!) and then each simulation type inheriting from SimulationTimeSeries.  This way, they could still spawn off the sub-time series and so on, but it would be slightly flatter.\n\nHowever, I don't think that should be necessary for accepting the PR.\n\nI'm excited about the prospect of having simulation-specific time series loading.  This is really great.  Let me know if you think flattening the class structure would be an improvement or not, and we can go from there.",
                "html": "<p>Hi Britton, I have reviewed the code changes.</p>\n<p>Overall, I like this direction.  I was a bit confused about the distinction between SimulationTimeSeries and TimeSeriesData, but I think I now understand it.  The SimulationTimeSeries acts as a \"value added\" mechanism of adding a few routines, as well as a self-registering mechanism, to simulation data.  This definitely works.</p>\n<p>One question I had was if you see this as potentially being a more flat relationship between the classes -- i.e., TimeSeriesData being the base class, with SimulationTimeSeries inheriting (and remaining basically the same!) and then each simulation type inheriting from SimulationTimeSeries.  This way, they could still spawn off the sub-time series and so on, but it would be slightly flatter.</p>\n<p>However, I don't think that should be necessary for accepting the PR.</p>\n<p>I'm excited about the prospect of having simulation-specific time series loading.  This is really great.  Let me know if you think flattening the class structure would be an improvement or not, and we can go from there.</p>\n",
                "markup": "creole"
            },
